program

# Store three animals with a common characteristic in a list
animals = ['dog', 'cat', 'rabbit']

# Print each animal name using a for loop
print("These animals have a common characteristic:")
for animal in animals:
    print(animal)

# Print a sentence about each animal using the animal name
print("\nEach of these animals would make a great pet:")
for animal in animals:
    print("A " + animal + " would make a great pet.")

# Print a final statement about the common characteristic
print("\nAny of these animals would make a great pet!")


output

These animals have a common characteristic:
dog
cat
rabbit

Each of these animals would make a great pet:
A dog would make a great pet.
A cat would make a great pet.
A rabbit would make a great pet.

Any of these animals would make a great pet!
